obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (68912)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Extension of Regulations and Acts in force in Saharanpur to Dehra Dun.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00092_187121_1661923541218&sectionId=68912&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00092_187121_1661923541218
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `The Regulations`
  line `and Acts now in force in the district of Saharanpur are hereby declared to extend to the said district of Dehra`
  line `Dun ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “and no judgment heretofore given, order passed or proceeding had in the said district, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `or to be invalid merely because any Regulation or Act, under or in reference to which such judgment, order or proceeding was`
  line `given, passed or had, was not in force at the time of such judgment, order or proceeding, was given, passed or had, was not in`
  line `force at the time of such judgement, order or proceeding, or on the ground of a defect of jurisdiction in ay Court or office” rep.`
  line `by Act 12 of 1891.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (68913)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Jurisdiction of High Court and Board of Revenue over Dehra Dun.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00092_187121_1661923541218&sectionId=68913&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00092_187121_1661923541218
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The High Court and`
  line `the Board of Revenue of ^1[Uttar Pradesh] shall exercise ^2*** respectively, in the said district, all the powers`
  line `which the said High Court or Board of Revenue are at present, respectively, authorized to exercise in any`
  line `part of ^1[Agra].`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs, by the A. O. 1950 for "the North-Western Provinces".`
  line
  line `2. The words "and shall be deemed to have been heretofore authorized to exercise" rep., ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (68914)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `District Court of Saharanpur to be District Court of Dehra Dun.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00092_187121_1661923541218&sectionId=68914&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00092_187121_1661923541218
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The District Court of`
  line `Saharanpur shall be ^1*** the District Court of such district until the State Government otherwise directs`
  line ^2***.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “deemed to have been heretofore the District Court of the said district of Dehra Dun and” rep., ibid.`
  line
  line `2. The words “and may subject to the provisions of Act 6 of 1871, hear appeals from decisions given in the said district before`
  line `the passing of this Act” rep. by Act 12 of 1891The words “and may subject to the provisions of Act 6 of 1871, hear appeals from decisions given in the said district before`
  line `the passing of this Act” rep. by Act 12 of 1891`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (68915)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Exemption of Jaunsar Bawar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00092_187121_1661923541218&sectionId=68915&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00092_187121_1661923541218
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall apply to that portion of the Dehra Dun`
  line `district called ^1Jaunsar Bawar ^2***`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. “Jaunsar Bawar” was one of the Scheduled Districts of the State of Uttar Pradesh, see the Scheduled Districts Act, 1874 (14 of`
  line `1874), First Schedule, Pt. IV, but has ceased to be so under the Constitution of India.`
  line
  line `2. The words “and referred to in s. 11 of Act 24 of 1864” rep. by Act 12 of 1891.`
